
Core MySQL Commands
🔹 Database Management
•	CREATE DATABASE dbname; → Create a new database
•	SHOW DATABASES;         → List all databases
•	USE dbname;             → Switch to a database/select database
•	DROP DATABASE dbname;   → Delete a database
> SYSTEM CLS;             → Clear Screen

🔹 Table Management
•	CREATE TABLE table_name (...);                    → Create a new table
•	SHOW TABLES;                                      → List tables in the current database
•	DESCRIBE table_name;                              → Show table structure
•	ALTER TABLE table_name ADD column_name datatype;  → Add a new column
•	ALTER TABLE table_name DROP column_name;          → Remove a column
•	DROP TABLE table_name;                            → Delete a table

🔹 Data Manipulation (DML)
•	INSERT INTO table_name VALUES (...);                → Insert new data
•	SELECT * FROM table_name;                           → Retrieve data (check data inside table)
•	UPDATE table_name SET column=value WHERE condition; → Update existing data
•	DELETE FROM table_name WHERE condition;             → Delete data

🔹 Data Definition (DDL)
•	CREATE INDEX idx_name ON table_name(column);        → Create an index
•	DROP INDEX idx_name ON table_name;                  → Remove an index

🔹 User & Privilege Management
•	CREATE USER 'username'@'host' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';   → Create a new user
•	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON dbname.* TO 'username'@'host';    → Grant permissions
•	REVOKE ALL PRIVILEGES ON dbname.* FROM 'username'@'host'; → Remove permissions
•	DROP USER 'username'@'host'; → Delete a user

🔹 MySQL Client Commands (special commands inside mysql> prompt)
•	\h → Help (list all commands)
•	\u dbname   → Switch database
•	\q          → Quit MySQL client
•	\c          → Clear current input
•	\d          → Set statement delimiter
•	\G          → Display query results vertically

