1️ Delete (DROP) a single column from a table
If you want to remove the column itself from the table structure:
ALTER TABLE table_name
DROP COLUMN column_name;

2️ Delete data from a single column (keep the column)
If you want to clear values in a column but keep the column:
UPDATE table_name
SET column_name = NULL;

3️ Delete data from a column with condition
Delete values only for specific rows:
UPDATE table_name
SET column_name = NULL
WHERE condition;

4️ Delete row(s) based on column value
If you want to delete entire rows based on a column:
DELETE FROM table_name
WHERE column_name = value;

5. modify column name
Use RENAME COLUMN (simplest and safest):
ALTER TABLE table_name
RENAME COLUMN old_column_name TO new_column_name;

6. Modify column name + datatype together + table name
ALTER TABLE users
CHANGE age user_age INT NOT NULL;
RENAME TABLE table_name TO new_table_name;

7.User Mysql
check available users : SELECT user, host FROM mysql.user

8. Import database in linux
mysql -u username -p database_name < backup.sql







